            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>1. Register your company on the eTenderwales portal (this is only required once).</P>
               <P>Browse to the eSourcing Portal: www.etenderwales.bravosolution.co.uk.</P>
               <P>Click the “Click here to register” link.</P>
               <P>Accept the terms and conditions and click “continue”.</P>
               <P>Enter your correct business and user details.</P>
               <P>Note the username you chose and click “Save” when complete.</P>
               <P>You will shortly receive an email with your unique password (please keep this secure).</P>
               <P>2. Express an Interest in the tender.</P>
               <P>Login to the portal with the username/password.</P>
               <P>Click the “Open Access PQQs/ITTs” link (These are Invitations to Tender open to any registered supplier).</P>
               <P>Click on the relevant ITT to access the content.</P>
               <P>Click the “Express Interest” button in the “Actions” box on the left-hand side of the page.</P>
               <P>This will move the PQQ/ITT into your “My PQQ/ITTs” page. (This is a secure area reserved for your projects only).</P>
               <P>Click on the PQQ/ITT code, you can now access any attachments by clicking the “Settings and Buyer Attachments” in the “Actions” box.</P>
               <P>3. Responding to the tender.</P>
               <P>You can now choose to “Reply” or “Reject” (please give a reason if rejecting);</P>
               <P>You can now use the ‘Messages' function to communicate with the buyer and seek any clarification;</P>
